"Schönwiese C.-D., Denhard M., Grieser J., Walter A.","Assessments of the global anthropogenic greenhouse and sulfate signal using different types of simplified climate models",1997,"Theoretical and Applied Climatology","57","1-2",,"119","124",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0002371098&partnerID=40&md5=ae957761799288654bfaecc29a9dc754","Inst. for Meteorology and Geophysics, University of Frankfurt/M., Germany; Inst. for Meteorology and Geophysics, J. W. Goethe University, P.O. Box 11 19 32, D-60054 Frankfurt/M., Germany","Schönwiese, C.-D., Inst. for Meteorology and Geophysics, University of Frankfurt/M., Germany, Inst. for Meteorology and Geophysics, J. W. Goethe University, P.O. Box 11 19 32, D-60054 Frankfurt/M., Germany; Denhard, M., Inst. for Meteorology and Geophysics, University of Frankfurt/M., Germany, Inst. for Meteorology and Geophysics, J. W. Goethe University, P.O. Box 11 19 32, D-60054 Frankfurt/M., Germany; Grieser, J., Inst. for Meteorology and Geophysics, University of Frankfurt/M., Germany, Inst. for Meteorology and Geophysics, J. W. Goethe University, P.O. Box 11 19 32, D-60054 Frankfurt/M., Germany; Walter, A., Inst. for Meteorology and Geophysics, University of Frankfurt/M., Germany, Inst. for Meteorology and Geophysics, J. W. Goethe University, P.O. Box 11 19 32, D-60054 Frankfurt/M., Germany","The problem of global climate change forced by anthropogenic emissions of greenhouse gases (GHG) and sulfur components (SU) has to be addressed by different methods, including the consideration of concurrent forcing mechanisms and the analysis of observations. This is due to the shortcoming and uncertainties of all methods, even in case of the most sophisticated ones. In respect to the global mean surface air temperature, we compare the results from multiple observational statistical models such as multiple regression (MRM) and neural networks (NNM) with those of energy balance (EBM) and general circulation models (GCM) where, in the latter case, we refer to the recent IPCC Report. Our statistical assessments, based on the 1866-1994 period, lead to a GHG signal of 0.8-1.3 K and a combined GHG-SU signal of 0.5-0.8 K detectable in observations. This is close to GCM simulations and clearly larger than the volcanic, solar and ENSO (El Niño/southern oscillation) signals also considered.",,,,,,,,"Allan, R.J., Nicholls, N., Jones, P.D., Butterworth, I.J., A further extension of the Tahiti-Darwin SOI, Early ENSO and Darwin Pressure (1991) J. Climate, 4, pp. 743-749; Bayer, D., Denhard, M., Meyhöfer, S., Rapp, J., Schönwiese, C.-D., (1994) Trend- und Multiple Signalanalyse Globaler Bzw. Europäischer Klimavariationen, 172p. , Frankfurt/M.: Bericht Nr. 98, Inst. Meteorol. Geophys. Univ; Cubasch, U., Hasselmann, K., Höck, M., Maier-Raimer, E., Miklolajewicz, U., Santer, B.D., Sausen, R., Time-dependant greenhouse warming computations with a coupled ocean-atmosphere model (1992) Climate Dyn., 8, pp. 55-69; Cubasch, U., Hegerl, G.C., Hellbach, A., Höck, H., Mikolajewicz, U., Santer, B.D., Voss, R., A climate change simulation starting from 1935 (1995) Climate Dyn., 11, pp. 71-84; Denhard, M., Walter, A., Schönwiese, C.-D., Simulationen globaler Klimavänderungen mit Hilfe neuronaler Netze (1996) Naturw. Rdsch., , in press; Foukal, P.V., Lean, J., An empirical model of total solar irradiance variation between 1874 and 1988 (1980) Science, 247, pp. 556-558; Grieser, J., Schönwiese, C.-D., Ein konzeptionelles Modell zum Studium verschiedener externer Einflüsse (1995) Ann. Meteorol., 31, pp. 78-79; Hasselmann, K., Sausen, R., Maier-Reimer, E., Voss, R., On the cold start problem in transient simulations with coupled atmosphere-ocean models (1993) Climate Dyn., 9, pp. 53-61; Hasselmann, K., Bengtsson, L., Cubasch, U., Hegerl, G.C., Rohde, H., Roeckner, E., Von Storch, H., Waszkewitz, J., (1995) Detection of Anthropogenic Climate Change Using a Fingerprint Method, pp. 20S. , Hamburg: Max-Planck-Inst. f. Meteorolo